description: TEHRAN – The German government has ordered the closure of the Islamic Center of Hamburg and its affiliated organizations across the country, citing accusations of propagating extremism and radical Islamic ideology.
title: Islamophobia on full display

description: TEHRAN- The Paris 2024 Olympic Games have been overshadowed by Israel’s participation amid the regime’s genocidal war on the Gaza Strip.
title: Paris Olympics: France, IOC turn a blind eye to Israeli apartheid

description: TEHRAN – Iran's Foreign Ministry spokesman Nasser Kanaani has vehemently condemned a report by former UN Special Rapporteur on the situation of human rights in Iran, Javaid Rehman, calling it "false" and a blatant attempt to damage the West Asian country’s image.
title: Ex-HR rapporteur serving terrorists: foreign ministry condemns Javaid Rehman’s anti-Iran report

description: TEHRAN – Ali Bahreini, Iran's ambassador and permanent representative to the United Nations office in Geneva, has issued a stark warning about the dangers posed by Israel's nuclear weapons program to global peace and security.
title: Tehran sounds alarm bell over Israel’s nuclear threat to global peace

description: TEHRAN –Yemeni armed forces will keep delivering significant strikes against the Israeli regime using their domestically produced weapons and equipment, the commander of the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC) Navy said on Tuesday.
title: Yemen will persist in fighting Israel using domestic resources: top Iranian commander

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s Minister of Intelligence, on Wednesday, announced the arrest of two ringleaders of the ISIS terrorist group.
title: Two ISIS ringleaders captured in anti-terror raids: Iranian Official

description: TEHRAN- Iran’s Guardian Council has validated the credentials of Masoud Pezeshkian and has forwarded them to the office of the Leader of the Islamic Revolution for Ayatollah Seyyed Ali Khamenei's review.
title: Guardian Council endorses Masoud Pezeshkian’s credentials

description: TEHRAN- The commander-in-chief of Iran’s Police, along with a group of officers and border officials, visited the Shalamcheh border terminal on Wednesday.
title: Iran's Police chief enters Shalamcheh ahead of Arbaeen walk

description: TEHRAN – In a recent development within the Islamic Revolution Guard Corps (IRGC), Brigadier General Ali Mohammad Naeini has been appointed as the new spokesman and deputy for public relations.
title: Brigadier General Ali Mohammad Naeini appointed as new IRGC spokesman

description: TEHRAN – Iran's United Nations ambassador has firmly denied accusations made by representatives of the United States, the United Kingdom, and France, condemning their silence on the Israeli regime’s aggressive actions against Yemen.
title: Iran rebuts allegations from U.S., UK, France, criticizes silence on Israeli aggression

description: TEHRAN-The play “An Ordinary Circuit” written by Jean-Claude Carrière will be staged in Rasht, capital of Gilan Province, for one week, from July 27 to August 2.
title: Jean-Claude Carrière’s “An Ordinary Circuit” to be performed in Rasht

description: TEHRAN-Eight short films from Iran will take part in the Regina International Film Festival and Awards (RIFFA) in Regina, Canada, due to be held from August 20 to 30.
title: 8 Iranian short films to attend Regina International Film Festival and Awards

description: Israel’s far-right minister Itamar Ben-Gvir has said Jewish people are allowed to pray at the Al-Aqsa Mosque, a statement that goes against a decades-long policy.
title: Islamic Jihad: Ben-Gvir’s comments “recipe for bloodshed”

description: TEHRAN - In a commentary published on July 22, the Guardian said Joe Biden, who on Sunday dropped out of the presidential race for the November elections, would be seen as a “lame duck”.
title: Biden would be seen as a lame duck: analysis

description: The Norwegian Refugee Council (NRC) says all hospitals in northern Gaza have been either damaged or destroyed.
title: Aid group: Nothing left that can resemble life in northern Gaza

description: China says it stands by Palestinians to restore their legitimate rights.
title: China vows continued support for Palestinian rights

description: Around 400 American Jews, including over a dozen rabbis, staged a sin-in  in a Capitol office building a day before Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s speech in the US Congress.
title: American Jews: Stop arming Israel, funding genocide

description: TEHRAN- Amid talks being held in the United States this week between a top American delegation and an Iraqi delegation, reports have emerged that the government of Iraqi Prime Minister Mohammad Shia al-Sudani wants U.S. occupation forces to leave Iraq as early as this year.
title: Iraq wants US troops out

description: More than 150,000 people have fled the Gazan city of Khan Younis since Monday, two UN agencies have said, the BBC reported.
title: Over 150,000 Palestinians flee Israel’s bloody onslaught in Khan Younis

description: TEHRAN - The Ministry of Cultural Heritage, Tourism, and Handicrafts is organizing a special cooking competition to highlight the culinary skills of people with disabilities.
title: Culinary competition for people with disabilities

description: TEHRAN – Putting some spark into Gilan’s tourism, the number of international flights to and from Rasht airport has significantly intensified over the past couple of months.
title: Intl. flights move up at Rasht airport

description: TEHRAN – A group of skilled motorcyclists will embark on a rally tour from Iran to Türkiye, starting on Friday morning, July 26.
title: Cyclists to traverse Iran-Türkiye route

description: TEHRAN - Restoration of the western wall of the historical Belqeys Castle in Esfarayen, North Khorasan, has officially commenced, according to the cultural heritage site’s director.
title: Belqeys Castle undergoes restoration

description: TEHRAN - As millions of pilgrims prepare for their annual on-foot journey to Iraq’s holy city of Karbala to commemorate Arbaeen, Kermanshah province has announced an increase in the number of handicraft stalls along the pilgrimage route.
title: Kermanshah handicrafts to be on view for Arbaeen trekkers

description: TEHRAN - The city of Dezful, sometimes referred to as the “city of bricks,” is a living museum of ancient Persian architecture, where every alley and corner reveals intricate designs and historical wonders.
title: Dezful Mosque: an example of Persian architectural mastery

description: TEHRAN - Despite a slight decrease in the number of athletes compared to the Tokyo Olympics, Iran's contingent is still set to make its mark at the 2024 Paris Games with 40 qualified athletes across 13 sports. Among them are fresh faces and young talents who could emerge as the breakout stars of this edition.
title: Iran at the 2024 Paris Olympics: A land of hope and glory awaits

description: TEHRAN- The 29th edition of Tehran Theater Festival has received 361 works from theater groups across the province.
title: Tehran Theater Festival receives over 350 submissions

description: TEHRAN- “Charade”, a 1963 romantic comedy film by American film director Stanley Donen, was reviewed at the Arasbaran Cultural Center in Tehran on Wednesday.
title: Tehran cultural center screens classic movie “Charade”

description: TEHRAN – Acting President Mohammad Mokhber has ordered government bodies to implement the national document on the development of artificial intelligence which had been ratified on June 18.
title: Govt. starts implementing national document on AI development

description: TEHRAN - World Drowning Prevention Day, declared in April 2021, is held annually on 25 July. Every year, an estimated 236,000 people drown, making drowning a major public health problem worldwide.
title: Drowning – a neglected public health issue

description: TEHRAN – For the first time in the country, DNA barcoding is being used to prepare genetic maps of endangered animal and plant species, an official from the Department of Environment has said.
title: DNA barcoding being used for specimen identification

description: TEHRAN- The director for planning and development in Iran’s National Petrochemical Company (NPC) said that the value chain projects in the petrochemical industry have been specified and introduced to the National Development Fund (NDF) for financing.
title: Petchem value chain projects specified, introduced to NDF

description: TEHRAN – Iran beat Chinese Taipei 3-0 (25-13, 25-12, 25-19) on Wednesday in the 2024 Asian Men's U20 Volleyball Championship.
title: Iran beat Taipei at 2024 Asian U20 Volleyball Championship

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji has said that over the past three years since the late President Raisi’s government took office the sanctions on the exports of gas condensate have been neutralized, Shana reported.
title: Sanctions on gas condensate exports neutralized: Oji

description: TEHRAN – Head of the Iranian Economy Ministry’s Production Financing Facilitation Center Majid Karimi says production-oriented investment and financing production units are the main requirements for achieving the country’s 8.0 percent economic growth target.
title: ‘Financing production, a must for achieving economic growth’

description: TEHRAN - The Statistical Center of Iran (SCI) has put the average inflation rate in the twelve-month period ended on July 21, which marks the end of the fourth Iranian calendar month Tir, at 35.5 percent, falling 0.6 percent from the figure for the twelve-month ended to the third month.
title: Inflation rate falls 0.6%

description: TEHRAN – The head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) said that in the first four months of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20-July 21) the country exported $17.5 billion non-oil goods, registering an 8.0 percent growth, year on year.
title: Iran’s non-oil exports increase 8% in 4 months y/y

description: TEHRAN – Iranian Finance and Economic Affairs Minister Ehsan Khandouzi has announced that the government is offering 400 trillion rials (about $800 million) of facilities to domestic producers, IRIB reported.
title: Govt. offers over $800m of facilities to producers

description: "It's very clear that China has entered a new era under President Xi Jinping. Reform is the hallmark of this new era and President Xi Jinping is the helmsman of reform, spearheading China's development, modernization and reform in the 21st century," said host Mushahid Hussain Sayed, former chairman of Pakistan's Senate Defense Committee on CGTN's show Global South Voices.
title: Global South applauds China's reform benefits and future

description: TEHRAN – Esteghlal football team will host Persepolis in Matchweek 6 of the 24th edition of the Iran’s Persian Gulf Professional League (PGPL).
title: 2024/25 PGPL: Tehran derby scheduled for Matchweek 6

description: TEHRAN – Iran men’s sitting volleyball team head coach Hadi Rezaei says that the world respects them and they are known as Dream Team.
title: Iran's nickname is Dream Team: Hadi Rezaei
